18/06/2007
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- The European Commission expressed satisfaction with the progress Macedonia has made in meeting the political and economic criteria necessary for EU integration, Deputy Prime Minister in charge of EU integration Gabriela Konevska-Trajkovska told reporters Sunday (June 17th). 
She briefed the media about the conclusions and recommendations of the EU-Macedonian Stabilisation and Association Committee, which met in Brussels last week. 
Macedonia hopes to receive a start date for accession negotiations with the EU this year.
In other news, the first-ever joint Macedonian-British military exercise starts on Monday at the Krivolak military grounds near Skopje. 
The drill aims to boost readiness to participate in NATO-led stabilisation and peacekeeping missions. 
(Vecer, Dnevnik - 18/06/07; MIA, Makfax, A1 TV - 17/06/07)
